Inspire Imitation		KEY:Half-Elf ~ Inspire Imitation	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RacialTraits.Half-Elf Racial Trait.SpecialQuality.Special Quality			PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Half-Elf ~ Inspire Imitation],[!PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,HalfElf_ReplaceAdaptability=true]							DESC:Whenever a half-elf succeeds at a skill check, she can inspire imitators as a swift action. Any ally within 30 feet who witnesses the successful check and attempts the same check within the next minute gains a +2 bonus on the check as if from the aid another action.	DESC:This racial trait replaces skilled.|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Half-Elf ~ Inspire Imitation																													COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.8																																									FACT:HalfElf_ReplaceAdaptability|true
Tenacious			KEY:Half-Orc ~ Tenacious		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RacialTraits.Half-Orc Racial Trait.SpecialQuality.Special Quality			PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Half-Orc ~ Tenacious],[!PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,HalfOrc_ReplaceOrcFerocity=true]									DESC:City-dwelling half-orcs must often be tenacious to get by. Once per day if a half-orc fails a Fortitude save, Will save, or Constitution check, he can reroll the save or check. The half-orc must take the second result, even if it is worse.	DESC:This racial trait replaces orc ferocity.|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Half-Orc ~ Tenacious																																			COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.9																																									FACT:HalfOrc_ReplaceOrcFerocity|true
